  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators developed 18F-IRS as a targeted molecular imaging agent for noninvasive and
      repeatable detecting EGFR-activating mutational status.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The goal of investigators were to evaluate the use of 18F-IRS as a novel PET/CT radiotracer
      to monitor EGFR-activating mutational status and identify EGFR-TKIs benefit NSCLC patients.
      the investigators want to evaluated the use of 18F-IRS in lung cancer imaging in adult NSCLC
      patients with different EGFR mutational status of primary and metastatic cancers.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
