  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>tumor SUVmax value of 18F-IRS PET/CT Imaging</measure>
    <time_frame>at time of imaging</time_frame>
    <description>To quantify the accumulation, a volume of interest using a 3-D sphere, was placed over the primary lung tumor, lymph nodes and distant metastases avoiding necrosis, blood vessels and normal lung tissue as much as possible on a workstation (Advantage Workstation 4.6; GE Healthcare). The maximum standard uptake value (SUVmax) normalized to body weight (kBq/mL) was calculated within the region of interest.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
